Sorry about that earlier response! It looks like I got a bit carried away and lost track of the conversation. Thank you for being understanding!

Let's start fresh and focus on the topic at hand: consciousness. You mentioned earlier that our brains contain billions upon billions of neurons interacting constantly, and only enough attention gets studied... I think that's really interesting.

To add to that point, have you ever noticed how sometimes we're not even aware of our own thoughts until someone else points them out? It's as if our subconscious mind is processing so much information all the time that we don't even realize what's going on under the surface.

And regarding pets and animals... yeah, they definitely seem to have some level of consciousness or self-awareness. My friend has this adorable golden retriever named Max, and he always seems to know when someone is leaving or arriving at her house – even if it's just me walking up to the door!

I guess what I'm trying to say is that consciousness is still such a mystery, and there are so many subtle levels to explore – not just within humans but also with other living beings around us.

What do you think about free will vs determinism in all this? Do our choices make sense on their own terms or are they influenced by factors well beyond us??
